   159	- **raiseFlag(n)** — the one routine that flips F(n) 0→1 and propagates the
   160	  flip through n's current K0∪K1 out-edges (§6.4).
   161	- **watcher** — `{setState, lastRendered, lastRenderSeq, notifiedMask}`;
   162	  value fields written at the commit edge only.
   163	- **pass / pin / lineage / retirement / episode** — fork-scoped pass with
   164	  yield/resume; pin = globalSeq at pass start; lineage = fork-minted stable
   165	  id per (root, batch-set) across restarts/replays (D11); retirement =
   166	  exactly-once fold; episode = quiescence to quiescence.
   167	- **staging list** — per-pass list of arena node ids minted during that
   168	  pass's renders; promotion/reclamation protocol §15.6 (S15).
   169	- **fold frame** — the execution frame active while an updater/reducer
   170	  callback runs during any fold; enforces O15's purity rule (§13.2).
   171	
   172	## 4. The mode protocol: DIRECT/LOGGED twin builds (SPK-H + SPK-Q remedies)
   173	
   174	Both spike rules triggered: SPK-H measured the two per-recompute hook
   175	null-checks at deep 1.025–1.035× min across 3 sessions (>1% rule); SPK-Q
   176	measured the NEWEST routing branch at reads 1.024–1.038× min (>2% rule,
   177	thin margin — the idle-machine rerun stays queued as the cheap challenge).
   178	Both costs are therefore **compiled out of DIRECT**, not branch-hidden. The
   179	rebuild protocol, precisely:
   180	
   181	1. **Two generated builds from one template.** The schema/codegen pipeline
   182	   (settled apparatus, D6) emits `buildDirect(state)` and
   183	   `buildLogged(state)` from one annotated source: regions tagged
   184	   `@logged-only` (write logging, routing, hooks, watcher tables) are absent
   185	   from the DIRECT output — not gated, absent. CI: regenerate-and-diff;
   186	   per-build bytecode budgets; a symbol scan asserting the DIRECT bundle
   187	   contains no tape/world/walk/hook identifiers.
   188	2. **State outlives builds.** The state record (plane buffers, side columns,
   189	   free lists, counters) is closure-external; each build binds its fields as
   190	   `const` at build time (the only binding at const parity [GUIDE]). Growth
   191	   already rebuilds closures at operation boundaries; the mode swap is the
   192	   same maneuver.
   193	3. **One mutable dispatch slot.** `engine.ops` is the single mutable field
   194	   on a const engine record; every public entry point (prototype methods on
   195	   Atom/Computed, `effect`, `batch`, `untracked`, `configure`) performs
   196	   exactly one `engine.ops.X(...)` load+call. The donor's measured numbers
   197	   already include this discipline (growth uses it) [ARENA]; user-held
   198	   function identities never change across the swap.
   199	4. **`registerReactBridge()`** asserts no eval frame, no walk, no open
   200	   `batch()` (throws "register the bridge during setup" otherwise);
   201	   allocates LOGGED-only state (empty tapes, K1 plane, clocks, watcher
   202	   tables, staging); sets `engine.ops = buildLogged(state)`; latches the
   203	   mode (monotonic — never back to DIRECT; S6/D1). Pending core-effect
   204	   queues are state, so they carry over.
   205	5. **Growth preserves mode**: `engine.ops = build[mode](grownState)`; a
   206	   conformance test grows the arena under LOGGED and asserts hooks/routing
   207	   still fire (the 179-suite runs inside a synthetic episode both before
   208	   and after growth).
   209	6. **The compiled-out inventory** (what LOGGED bodies add): write body =
   210	   guard + token + receipt + clock + walk (§5.1); read body = one
   211	   `currentWorld` check + §6.2 routing; recompute body = `beforeRetrack` /
   212	   `afterRetrack` inline (guarded by one live-batch check, LOGGED-only);
   213	   watch/unwatch body = watcher table maintenance. DIRECT bodies are donor
   214	   bodies, byte-for-byte modulo codegen whitespace.
   215	7. **The residual is a measured question, not a claim**: LOGGED-quiet (React
   216	   mounted, no transitions) now carries the branch and hook costs that
   217	   DIRECT no longer does. Gate G-Q (≤2% tier-0) binds the LOGGED-quiet
   218	   build; **SPK-L** (§16) measures it. Mitigation ladder if it fails, all
   219	   within-LOGGED: fuse `F∧CT` into one status load; hoist the world check
   220	   into the per-pass entry (routing chosen once per pass segment, not per
   221	   read) — never a watcher-count key (S6).
   222	
   223	P3's clause "pure-core users execute zero concurrency instructions" is now
   224	literal: the instructions do not exist in the build they run.
