   471	snapshots evaluate `w = committed-for-root`. Thenable entries use the
   472	prefix variant (§9.2). The watcher comparator uses direct value comparison
   473	against a fresh fold at reconcile time (no retained fingerprint to rot).
   474	
   475	### 8.3 Fingerprints: minted stamps, never recomputed encodings (B1 kill)
   476	
   477	```
   478	fingerprint(atom, w)     = max(seq of newest w-visible tape entry (0 if none),
   479	                               atom.baseSeq, atom.reducerStamp)
   480	fingerprint(computed, w) = M(computed, wKey(w)).valueStamp   // recompute dep first if invalid
   481	```
   482	
   483	- `baseSeq` moves ONLY forward, at fold time, to the max folded seq (§5.3).
   484	  The B1 collapse — tape empties at compaction, "newest visible entry"
   485	  reverts to 0, matching a pre-write recording — is dead: after compaction
   486	  the base term reports exactly the seq the folded entry reported before.
   487	  Pre/post-compaction fingerprints are IDENTICAL for worlds that saw the
   488	  entry (no spurious recompute) and MOVED for worlds that newly see it via
   489	  the retired clause (necessary recompute). Old-pinned worlds are safe by
   490	  pin-gated compaction: an entry invisible to a live pin cannot compact, so
   491	  its absence can never be misread (C7 walk).
   492	- `valueStamp` is minted `++globalSeq` whenever a recompute produces a
   493	  value not `isEqual` to the memo's previous value (per-world equality
   494	  cutoff), and fresh on memo creation. Because stamps are minted from the
   495	  shared monotone line and never locally reset, a recreated memo can never
   496	  reproduce an older stamp — cross-generation ladder compares fail CLOSED
   497	  (recompute), never open. The champion's unstated hazard (memo death and
   498	  recreation reusing small per-memo version numbers) is unrepresentable.
   499	- `fnStamp` / `reducerStamp`: minted at identity swap (§13.1, §13.3).
   500	- Cost: the atom fingerprint is one tape-tail inspection + two column loads
   501	  + max; the predicate is int compares. Gate G-V (§16.1).
   502	
   503	### 8.4 Worked B1 schedule (the fingerprint walk; full C16/C12 walks in §17)
   504	
   505	Effect E depends on atom `a` (never written): snapshot records `(a, fp=0)`.
   506	Batch k writes `a=1` (entry seq s1); k retires committed; compaction folds
   507	the entry, tape empties, `baseSeq := s1`. Flush check: `fp(a, committed) =
   508	max(0-none, s1, 0) = s1 ≠ 0` → re-run, effect sees 1. Round-1 predicate
   509	computed `fp = 0` (no visible entry, no base term) `== 0` recorded → effect
   510	never re-ran (C16/C12 silently broken). The repair is structural, not a
   511	special case: no fingerprint is ever derived from a representation that
   512	compaction can revert.
