   514	## 9. Suspense: lineage identity × content validity (I20, TKC-2, O17 pins)
   515	
   516	### 9.1 The key (D11, unchanged) and the new conjunct
   517	
   518	`ctx.use(thenable)` inside a world evaluation resolves through the
   519	positional cache keyed `(node, lineageId, position)` — lineage is fork fact
   520	F5, stable across restarts/replays of one (root, batch-set), distinct
   521	across set changes, dead at commit/abandon. Identity alone was round 1's
   522	answer; I20 showed identity without content validity replays a thenable
   523	fetched from a stale world after an intra-batch write (lineage does not
   524	change when the SET's members write again — that is what it is for).
   525	
   526	### 9.2 Content validity: the dep-fingerprint prefix (I20 repair)
   527	
   528	Each cache entry additionally records `prefixDeps = [(id, fp)]`: the
   529	tracked reads this evaluation performed BEFORE reaching this `ctx.use`
   530	position, with their §8.3 fingerprints at record time. On a later
   531	evaluation reaching position p:
   532	
   533	```
   534	entry = cache[(node, lineage, p)]
   535	if entry exists ∧ entry.gen == lineage.gen
