   543	
   544	Both required properties hold: **stable identity across pure retries**
   545	(purity ⇒ same reads, same order, unmoved fingerprints ⇒ pairwise match);
   546	**invalidate on included write** (a write to any slot in the world's mask
   547	that touched a prefix dep moves that dep's fingerprint ⇒ mismatch ⇒
   548	refetch from the new world's content). Strictly better than coarse: an
   549	included write that provably cannot feed the fetch (not in the read prefix)
